The paper proposes a new form of variational autoencoder (VAE) and presents extensive experiments on image benchmark datasets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of adversarial training, which is a common technique in the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE) and information theory (cs.IT).
